4
00:00:24,902 --> 00:00:27,358
I'll start by reminding you briefly
about the overall 

5
00:00:27,558 --> 00:00:29,473
technology innovation process.

6
00:00:29,673 --> 00:00:32,070
Basically, the technology
innovation process

7
00:00:32,281 --> 00:00:38,587
comprises three broad phases: the concept,
feasibility, and the implementation phases.

8
00:00:38,787 --> 00:00:42,532
Phase one is the concept development
phase, which involves

9
00:00:42,732 --> 00:00:46,888
a variety of issues, such as:
defining your mission,

10
00:00:48,132 --> 00:00:53,122
choosing your pilot country origin,
engaging local stakeholders,

11
00:00:53,322 --> 00:00:59,021
taking stock of alternative products,
and then defining your product specs.

12
00:00:59,706 --> 00:01:02,248
Phase two is
the feasibility phase

13
00:01:02,448 --> 00:01:04,702
where you attempt to test
and demonstrate

14
00:01:04,902 --> 00:01:07,674
the feasibility of your product
concept and business model.

15
00:01:08,271 --> 00:01:11,434
This may end up requiring you
to readjust your product concepts

16
00:01:11,634 --> 00:01:12,858
and business strategy.

17
00:01:13,058 --> 00:01:15,929
And phase three
is about implementation

18
00:01:16,129 --> 00:01:18,771
that is actually bringing
the products to the market,

19
00:01:18,971 --> 00:01:22,183
where you will aim to reach
your break even stage,

20
00:01:22,383 --> 00:01:24,570
and then scaling up to other region.

21
00:01:25,244 --> 00:01:27,770
This is also the phase where
you will need to diligently

22
00:01:27,970 --> 00:01:31,040
 carry out impact monitoring
activities, in order to ensure 

23
00:01:31,240 --> 00:01:34,742
that you advance towards
your original mission.

24
00:01:35,708 --> 00:01:38,527
For each of the phases there
is one key message:

25
00:01:39,569 --> 00:01:43,257
For the concept phase
the main message is to LEARN,

26
00:01:43,936 --> 00:01:47,366
for the feasibility phase the main
message is to COLLABORATE 

27
00:01:47,898 --> 00:01:52,707
while for implementation
we say "BE AGILE".

28
00:01:53,895 --> 00:01:57,900
For the rest of this lecture we'll
only focus on the Concept phase.

29
00:01:59,073 --> 00:02:02,065
The concept phase can
be broadly divided into the following parts

30
00:02:02,265 --> 00:02:04,601
